These are Puzzles for 5x4 Level 8

.:: Puzzle 5x4-Level-8-1::.
There are 4 different favourite colors: apricot, emerald, white, grey
The people grow 4 different varities of flowers: dahlia, orchid, tulip, marigold
4 different games are played: chess, go, billiard, snooker
There are 4 different nationalities: argentine, colombian, indonesian, indian
The people's birthday is in 4 different months: march, february, september, may
 1. the indonesian is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in may##3
 2. the person who likes white is somewhere to the left of the person who growsmarigold##5
 3. the person who growsorchid is on the far left##1
 4. the person who growsdahlia is the colombian##1
 5. the person who's birthday is in september is on the right of the person who growsdahlia##1
 6. the colombian is not to the left of the person who's birthday is in february##8
 7. the indonesian is on the right of the person playing go##1
 8. the indonesian is not to the left of the person who's birthday is in march##8
 9. the person who's birthday is in may is the person who likes apricot##1
10. the person who likes grey is somewhere to the left of the person who likes emerald##5
11. the person who likes emerald is in an even position##4
12. the person who's birthday is in september is on the left or right of the person who's birthday is in march##3
13. the person playing snooker is not to the right of the person who likes white##8
14. the person who's birthday is in september is somewhere to the left of the person who's birthday is in may##5
15. the colombian is somewhere to the left of the indonesian##5
16. the person playing billiard is on the left of the indian##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |    1     |     2     |      3       |      4      |
| Color    | grey | emerald     | white     | apricot |
| Flower        | orchid  | dahlia | tulip      | marigold      |
| Game         | snooker  | go    | billiard | chess       |
| Nationality       | argentine | colombian   | indonesian      | indian  |
| Birthday   | february      | march  | september   | may      |

